 full traffic report oil and gas refining go  twitter reddit pinterest  email print tumblr linkedin stumbleupon tweet follow httpstwittercomdailybreezenews home â news â business â oil and gas refining exxonmobil exits torrance as pbf energy assumes ownership and operation of refinery torrance mayor pat furey center with new torrance refining company executives jeff dill and pbf western region president ceo tom nimbley left and steve steach refinery manager right the transition ceremony marked the takeover of the exxonmobil plant in torrance by the new torrance refining company july   brad graverson  staff photographer by nick green daily breeze posted   pm pdt  updated on   comments pbf ceo tom nimbley spoke at the transition ceremony for the new torrance refining company as it takes over the exxonmobil plant in torrance july   brad graverson  staff photographer pbf energy officially assumed ownership friday of the exxonmobil torrance refinery bringing an end to the oil giant’s catastrophic final  months in charge of the aging plant after a february  explosion shattered the confidence of residents in the company’s ability to operate it safely pbf unveiled new whiteandblue signs at a brief ribboncutting ceremony friday while pledging to operate the plant now called the torrance refining co refinery in a safe reliable and environmentally responsible manner “i really have empathy for the people of torrance” said ceo and chairman tom nimbley “it’s been a difficult  months for them torrance was always viewed as the best refinery in the state it’s our intention to get it back to that level”the pledge of reliability was put to the test early when company and city officials struggled to remove a securely fastened covering to unveil the sign a burly worker eventually gave it the requisite hard tug to finish the jobassemblyman david hadley put the event in context in a statement read by former councilman tom brewer now a member of the republican’s district staff “let’s be honest about this” he said “this is not a celebration it’s a transition this is not a victory lap it’s a chance for a new beginning here in torrance and we’re cheering you on to succeed“your predecessor lost significant confidence and goodwill in the community in recent years” hadley’s statement said “it’s sad to say this but that’s true we want you to succeed and we’ll cheer you on but we want you first and foremost to protect the safety of the people in the south bay”exxonmobil’s safety record since the blast frightened many members of the community and prompted the formation of no fewer than three grassroots groups that are demanding safety improvements both state and federal investigators have blamed exxonmobil for the blast including citing a deliberate decision not to fix equipment the company knew could cause a lifethreatening explosionthe state has fined the company more than  while the us chemical safety board issued subpoenas to the company in an effort to uncover more information in the blast’s wakeexxonmobil has appealed the fine and numerous state citations while also ignoring some csb subpoenas much to the anger of politicians like rep ted lieu dmanhattan beach a former torrance city council member advertisement the south coast air quality management district also is conducting a study to determine whether an alternative to extremely toxic modified hydrofluoric acid is viable for use at the refinery the acid forms a toxic groundhugging gas at room temperature that could kill thousands in the densely populated area during an accidental releasecsb officials have said a catastrophic release of the acid was only averted during the explosion when debris hit scaffolding erected for future maintenance around a large vessel containing mhf exxonmobil has only reluctantly communicated with city residents since the explosion largely when compelled to by government officials holding public hearings on the explosionno exxonmobil official played a formal role in friday’s ribboncutting although a member of its public relations staff was on hand to take photospublic confidence was further eroded by a series of relatively minor accidents since the magnitude blast that literally rocked the city showered neighborhoods with industrial debris and increased gas pump prices the incidents included an accidental release of highly toxic modified hydrofluoric acid and just last week the collapse of a ton crane pbf already has taken steps to improve community outreachworkers friday were seen tending to the unkempt landscaping around the refinery that was a source of complaints by community leaders before last year’s explosion convinced many they had bigger problems to deal with at the plant than aestheticspbf has also used delays in the ownership transfer — originally scheduled to close in the first quarter — to reach out to a variety of community organizations including “a lot of groups our predecessor did not have a dialogue with” said jeffrey dill president of pbf energy western region llc “everything falls into place when the refinery is running reliably people are kept safe we are a good member of the community and that’s the place we want to be” dill saidin addition pbf has committed to an independent thirdparty review of the refinery to see if any improvements are recommended and plans to extend an automated monitoring system of the mhf unit to the city fire department dill said that monitoring system is already tied in to equipment at the aqmdwith the  million purchase of the barrelperday refinery that was announced last year pbf increases its refining capacity to about  barrels of crude a day making it north america’s fourthlargest independent refiner in addition to the acre north torrance refinery pbf has acquired a network of pipelines storage facilities and distribution terminalsthose pipelines send crude oil from the ports of long beach and los angeles to the refinery while jet fuel is sent from the refinery to los angeles international airportpbf also acquired a mile crude gathering and transportation system which delivers san joaquin valley crude oil directly from the oil field to the refinerydill said pbf plans further investment to improve the refinery next year a major maintenance project is planned to overhaul the half of the refinery that wasn’t shut down by the explosion pbf stock closed friday at  on the new york stock exchange up  cents click here to subscribe to digital  home delivery   off about the author reporter covering torrance lomita rolling hills estates palos verdes estates nick also covers soccer as a sports columnist reach the author at nickgreendailybreezecom or follow nick on twitter lasoccerblog nickgreen full bio and more articles by nick green back to top galleries pbf takes over torrance refinery related torrance fire chief human error caused crane collapse at refinery top stories ‹ › most popular day week news sports biz ae email life please enable javascript to view the comments powered by disqus torrance refinery this is a custom widget this sliding bar can be switched on or off in theme options and can take any widget you throw at it or even fill it with your custom html code its perfect for grabbing the attention of your viewers choose between    or  columns set the background color widget divider color activate transparency a top border or fully disable it on desktop and mobile this is a custom widget this sliding bar can be switched on or off in theme options and can take any widget you throw at it or even fill it with your custom html code its perfect for grabbing the attention of your viewers choose between    or  columns set the background color widget divider color activate transparency a top border or fully disable it on desktop and mobile toggle slidingbar area home admin t welcome check out our new site hello neighbor view article learn about pbf energy and the torrance refinery click here have questions click here to send us an inquiry or cal