sce switching station to the existing refinery electrical distribution system this phase i is expected to improve sce’s reliability in phase ii torrance refining company will install new local substations and perform upgradesmodifications to the plant’s electrical distribution system which will be scheduled to coincide with future unit shutdowns to support continued safe reliable and environmentally responsible operations the project is currently in the permit approval process view recent updates archive permalink gallery company awards  to local teachers for innovative steam classroom grants in the community company awards  to local teachers for innovative steam classroom grantstorrance refining company llc torc in partnership with the torrance unified school district tusd hosted a teacher recognition event on june  at its torrance refinery to showcase demonstrations of innovative curriculum funded by the by admin t june nd categories in the community commentsread more setting the record straight jeff dill – our priorities tim shepperd – why mhf works marie wright – examples jatin shah – risk management curt lawrence by admin t april th categories in the community commentsread more company  pbf energy pbf energy search form search nyse  pbf    homecompanycolumn refinerieslogisticssafetymanagement teamboard of directorscustomerscolumn customer allocation viewernew customerlocationstariffsask a representativeproductscolumn clean fuelslubespetrochemicalslpgcommunitycareerscolumn careers  locationssearch our careersinvestorscolumn corporate governancestock  financial informationsec filingsevents calendarcolumn webcasts  presentationsinvestor faqinvestor contactannual report and proxy materialsnewscontact us home companycolumn refineries logistics safety management team board of directors customerscolumn customer allocation viewer new customer locations tariffs ask a representative productscolumn clean fuels lubes petrochemicals lpg community careerscolumn careers  loca